   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "487395c6-751a-4852-bdfb-a9b25ae8a743",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "DATA PRE PROCESSING"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1c3f2794-845c-4433-93bb-b6e489e1f3b1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The attributes with non numerical data are encoded to numerical data manually."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "f31abd7c-b804-488e-832d-0ba914c35bb3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "data.Sex.replace(to_replace=['male', 'female'], value=[1, 0], inplace=True)\n",
    "data.Embarked.replace(to_replace=['S', 'C', 'Q'], value=[\n",
    "                      0, 1, 2], inplace=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ec4780ab-e6a4-41e9-b2c6-4e0903400100",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The rows with outliers are then dropped from the dataset."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "0dbf13fe-f4c8-4293-ba62-6c958042880a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "for i in [i for i in data.columns]:\n",
    "    if data[i].nunique() >= 12:\n",
    "        Q1 = data[i].quantile(0.20)\n",
    "        Q3 = data[i].quantile(0.80)\n",
    "        IQR = Q3 - Q1\n",
    "        data = data[data[i] <= (Q3+(1.5*IQR))]\n",
    "        data = data[data[i] >= (Q1-(1.5*IQR))]\n",
    "data = data.reset_index(drop=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "977b1f7b-c18c-4f25-922f-238c394b7b4c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "SMOTE technique is used to balance the dataset to get equal number of the target variables."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "id": "54fd82b3-720a-48cf-b208-5ddfe0884384",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from imblearn.over_sampling import SMOTE\n",
    "x_cols = ['Pclass', 'Sex', 'Fare', 'Embarked']\n",
    "y_col = 'Survived'\n",
    "\n",
    "x = data[x_cols]\n",
    "y = data[y_col]\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "smote = SMOTE()\n",
    "X, Y = smote.fit_resample(x, y)\n",
    "data = pd.DataFrame(X, columns=x_cols)\n",
    "data[y_col] = Y"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "id": "fcc3412d-8fa1-4b16-9f8d-ddd8e8459802",
   "metadata": {},

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2e7f6576-d122-42d2-a8cf-aeb2d5bb5e4a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We then split the data into training and testing datasets in the ratio 80:20."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "id": "6a542faa-1a6e-4a47-aeda-efdc9bf5b442",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "\n",
    "x = data[x_cols]\n",
    "y = data[y_col]\n",
    "\n",
    "x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(x, y, train_size=0.8, test_size=0.2, random_state=0)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "69e298cd-5467-4e60-ba54-00176b3eab65",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The data is standardized using StandardScaler."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "id": "a6a3aa70-29da-42b3-878e-d929e14101ce",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
    "\n",
    "std = StandardScaler()\n",
    "\n",
    "x_train_std = std.fit_transform(x_train)\n",
    "x_train_std = pd.DataFrame(x_train_std, columns=x_cols)\n",
    "\n",
    "x_test_std = std.fit_transform(x_test)\n",
    "x_test_std = pd.DataFrame(x_test_std, columns=x_cols)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "14d69dce-37b4-49ae-835d-d1a196f10dbf",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Model Building and Testing"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2c158155-1046-44a8-9fd2-871a54ddee3f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "DecisionTree classifier is used to fit and predict the data."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "id": "36955c52-a812-424d-8617-14eb613a7052",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier\n",
    "\n",
    "clf = DecisionTreeClassifier()\n",
    "clf = clf.fit(x_train_std, y_train)\n",
    "y_pred = clf.predict(x_test_std)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "11ecf595-8381-4fe7-a575-072aa8083006",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The confusion matrix and classification report are used to evaluate the model."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "id": "19cdc41a-30c1-494b-869e-d960e09c067e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "              precision    recall  f1-score   support\n",
      "\n",
      "           0       0.72      0.83      0.77        75\n",
      "           1       0.81      0.70      0.75        79\n",
      "\n",
